# Required checks for this project

Before considering a task complete, run the project's quality checks and fix any failures.

## Commands (from repo root)

- **Lint (all):** `make lint`  
  Or individually: `uv run black --check app tests`, `uv run isort --check-only app tests`, `uv run flake8 app tests`, `uv run mypy app`
- **Fix formatting only:** `make lint-fix` (black + isort)
- **Unit tests (no DB):** `make test` or `uv run pytest -m "not requires_db" -v`
- **Dependency audit:** `make audit-deps` or `uv run pip-audit`

## What to do

1. After editing code, run `make lint` and fix any black, isort, flake8, or mypy issues.
2. Run `make test` and fix any failing tests.
3. Optionally run `make audit-deps` to confirm no known dependency vulnerabilities.

CI runs the same checks (see `.github/workflows/ci.yml`). Keeping local lint and tests passing avoids CI failures.
